B. Location Based Pairing Scheme
The above mentioned cooperative reader scheme can interfere with the received signal with low channel quality. Therefore, we propose a simple location based tag–reader paring scheme.
Transmission process is the same as in cooperative reader scheme in Fig. 3. In the location based pairing scheme, the controller compares the BER value of each reader and multiple readers in the threshold selection step by received test pilot from the k∗-th tag. If there is an extremely good channel gain between the tag and the reader, it is decided as a distributed mode which receives the signal with the best reader. In other

cases, it is determined as a centralized mode which receives the signal with multiple versions.

