V. CONCLUSIONS
In this paper, we proposed a cooperative scheme and a simple location based tag–reader paring scheme to improve decoding performance in ambient backscatter communication networks. Numerical results show that the more the number of readers is the better performance of reception reliability in general situation, but when there is an extremely close to the tag, there is a difference in the reliability of the received signal. Therefore, if a tag with extremly dominant channel gain exists, a method of receiving from a single reader is optimal.
For further work, there will be the tag signal detection that removes the inﬂuence of interference in a unknown channel environment

